 UB at a Glance 
UB is New York State’s flagship and one of the nation’s leading public research universities, recognized for our excellence and our impact.
Rankings and Pride PointsWho We AreBy the Numbers
Programs and SchoolsOur People
Our CampusesOur ResearchOur Financial ImpactEstimated Costs
 Rankings and Pride Points 
 Top 1% in the World 
Ranked No. 293 out of 19,788 universities worldwide by the Center for World University Rankings.
 Best of the Best 
As an AAU member, recognized as one of the leading North American universities engaged in the highest levels of research.
 No. 1 Public 
The top public university in New York State and No. 31 in the nation, according to the WSJ/THE College Rankings.
 New York’s Flagship 
Recognized for advancing the state’s public higher education mission as a leading center for academics and research.
   Find out more about our World-Class Reputation   
 Who We Are 
 
Name University at Buffalo
 The State University of New York		   
Affiliation New York State’s flagship, UB is the largest and most comprehensive campus in the 64-campus SUNY system. It is a member of the Association of American Universities.   
Founded 1846   
Overview UB is a premier, research-intensive public university dedicated to academic excellence. Our research, creative activity and people positively impact the world. Like the city we call home, UB is distinguished by a culture of resilient optimism, resourceful thinking and pragmatic dreaming that enables us to reach others every day.   
President Satish K. Tripathi 
Athletics Division I, Mid-American Conference 
Mascot Victor E. Bull

Alumni

 Our People 
 World-Renowned Faculty 
Our faculty have won many prestigious awards, including:
  • Nobel Prize
  • Pulitzer Prize
  • National Book Award
  • National Medal of Science
  • MacArthur Foundation “genius award”
 Notable Alumni 
Here are just a few of our celebrated graduates:
  • Award-winning journalist for CNN — Wolf Blitzer
  • Co-founder of the largest Chinese-language search engine — Li Yanhong (Robin Li)
  • Co-founder and partner of Orangetheory Fitness — Ellen Latham
  • Superstar NFL linebacker — Khalil Mack
  • Executive producer and host of NPR’s “Fresh Air” — Terry Gross
 Our Campuses 
Located in the Buffalo-Niagara region of upstate New York, UB has three distinct but closely connected campuses.
  •     9/7/22  Our campuses   
  •     3/2/22  Buffalo-Niagara   
  •     3/2/22  UB maps   
North Campus: Suburban Academic Center
 Amherst, New York
South Campus: Classic Neighborhood Setting
 Buffalo, New York
Downtown Campus: Dynamic Urban Presence
 Buffalo, New York
 Our Research 
We seek knowledge that leads to new cures, improved processes, stronger materials, faster computers, smarter software, smaller machines and thousands of other improvements. Our faculty have contributed to life-changing inventions including a test for cancer, pattern recognition software, and a 3-D viewer and data transmission system.
